### ============================================================================
### DrasiLib MQTT Reaction - HTTP Source Events
### ============================================================================
### Use with VS Code REST Client.
###
### Bootstrap data in bootstrap_data.jsonl starts with:
### AAPL, MSFT, GOOGL, TSLA, NVDA
###
### HTTP source endpoint:
###   POST /sources/stock-prices/events
###   POST /sources/stock-prices/events/batch
###
### MQTT topic format emitted by the reaction:
###   stocks/<query_name>/added
###   stocks/<query_name>/updated
###   stocks/<query_name>/deleted
### ============================================================================

### Health check
GET http://localhost:9000/health

###

### Update existing bootstrap row: AAPL (was 175.50 / 173.00)
POST http://localhost:9000/sources/stock-prices/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "operation": "update",
  "element": {
    "type": "node",
    "id": "price_AAPL",
    "labels": ["stock_prices"],
    "properties": {
      "symbol": "AAPL",
      "price": 179.10,
      "previous_close": 173.00,
      "volume": 6400000
    }
  }
}

###

### Update existing bootstrap row: TSLA (was 245.00 / 250.00)
POST http://localhost:9000/sources/stock-prices/events
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "operation": "update",
  "element": {
    "type": "node",
    "id": "price_TSLA",
    "labels": ["stock_prices"],
    "properties": {
      "symbol": "TSLA",
      "price": 257.20,
      "previous_close": 250.00,
      "volume": 9100000
    }
